---
title: Nuxt (Vue)
name: Nuxt (Vue)
description: Send email from a Nuxt server route with the top-level mail().
category: Frameworks
---

Postboi is framework-agnostic â€” read the request's `FormData` in a Nitro server route and
hand it straight to [`mail()`](/api). Postboi extracts the
[special fields](/formdata#special-fields) and renders the rest into a tidy HTML table.

```typescript
// server/api/contact.post.ts
import { mail } from 'postboi';

export default defineEventHandler(async (event) => {
	const form = await readFormData(event);

	// Reply-to comes from the submitted email, so replying reaches the sender.
	form.set('_reply_to', String(form.get('contactâ†’email') ?? ''));
	form.set('_subject', 'Contact Form');

	await mail({ body: form });
	return sendRedirect(event, '/?sent=1', 303);
});
```

`defineEventHandler`, `readFormData`, and `sendRedirect` are Nuxt auto-imports. Point a
`multipart/form-data` form at the route with fields like `contactâ†’name`, `contactâ†’email`,
and `detailsâ†’message` â€” the [`fieldsetâ†’field`](/formdata#grouped-fields) syntax groups them.

The provider and default recipient come from [`postboi.config.ts`](/config) â€” a
`POSTBOI_TOKEN` routes to [Postboi Cloud](/cloud), or pick any [provider](/providers).

**Runnable example:** [`examples/nuxt-provider-postboi`](https://github.com/darbymanning/postboi/tree/main/examples/nuxt-provider-postboi).
